Step 1. Calculate the Quick Assets. Quick assets exclude Inventory. They are the sum of:
 • Cash on Hand = 3,537,257.19  
 • Bank Deposits = 4,579,000.00  
 • Interest Receivable = 14,869.76  
 • Accounts Receivable = 1,716,911.17  

Sum of Quick Assets = 3,537,257.19 + 4,579,000.00 + 14,869.76 + 1,716,911.17 = 9,848,038.12

Step 2. The Total Current Liabilities (End_amount) is given as = 967,271.87

Step 3. Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 9,848,038.12 / 967,271.87 ≈ 10.18

Step 4. Calculate Net Profit Margin.  
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

Net Profit (from income statement) = 963,263.19  
Total Revenue = 3,025,437.82  

Thus, Net Profit Margin = (963,263.19 / 3,025,437.82) × 100% ≈ 31.84%

Final Answer in the required JSON format:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "10.18",
    "Net Profit Margin": "31.84%"
  }
}
